# PortSentinel AI — environment configuration example.
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in as needed. Everything here is
# OPTIONAL: with no env file the app runs with the AI assistant offline and the
# Esri satellite basemap on (falling back to the bundled vector map offline).

# ─── AI assistant (server-side, no VITE_ prefix) ──────────────────────────────
# Read by the /api/chat serverless proxy. Without it the chat degrades to
# "assistant offline" and the rule/decision UI still works.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ─── Satellite basemap (client-side, VITE_ prefix, GR-8 / D-88) ───────────────
# Which imagery provider the Maritime Network draws. Default: esri (keyless).
# esri     — Esri World Imagery, no key required (default)
# maptiler — requires VITE_MAPTILER_KEY
# mapbox   — requires VITE_MAPBOX_TOKEN
# custom   — requires VITE_SATELLITE_TILE_URL
# none     — disable imagery, use the bundled vector basemap only (pure offline)
# VITE_SATELLITE_PROVIDER=esri

# Keyed providers. Restrict these keys to your deploy domain(s) in the provider
# dashboard (HTTP-referrer / allowed-origin restriction) before shipping — the
# key is embedded in client tile URLs and is visible to anyone using the app.
# VITE_MAPTILER_KEY=
# VITE_MAPBOX_TOKEN=

# Custom XYZ raster source (must be a legitimate provider you are licensed to use):
# VITE_SATELLITE_TILE_URL=https://tiles.example.com/{z}/{x}/{y}.jpg
# VITE_SATELLITE_ATTRIBUTION=© Example Imagery
# VITE_SATELLITE_MAX_ZOOM=19
